{{see|Freecycle}}
==English==

===Etymology===
[[Blend]] of '''[[free]]''' and '''[[recycle]]'''
[[Category:Portmanteaus|freecycle]]


===Noun===
{{en-noun|s}}

#{{slang}} A group that engages in freecycling.
#: ''What '''freecycle''', did you join?''

====Usage notes====
According to The Freecycle Network, ''Freecycle''&trade; is properly used only as a brand name to identify the company’s products and services, ie a Freecycle group.


===Verb===
{{en-verb|freecycles|freecycling|freecycled}}

#{{slang}} To recycle by giving away an item for free.
#:''I '''freecycled''' most of the junk cluttering my house''.

